(13, 5, 'my_answer', 'In Mullaly, Thompson (1997) "outlines a number if assumptions and stereotypes about elderly people that reflect and reinforce ageism. They are often treated as childlike ill, lonely, asexual, poor, unintelligent" (p.214) I agree that these are the societal beliefs regarding the elderly. Once you have reached an older age I feel that society views you as no longer useful.\r\n\r\nI come from a town in rural Manitoba with a prevalent aging population. We were always taught to respect elders and that they are knowledgeable. I am sure there were times that some of these stereotypes came out or I might have had a few negative assumptions but there were so many examples that contradicted these stereotypes they did not stick.\r\n\r\nI feel that growing up where the elderly was the norm I have not been influenced as much by the negative stereotypes regarding the elderly.'),
